parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, slip into neutral, or become stuck in gear, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle drives sluggishly
the transmission fault light turns on
the vehicle loses speed
the vehicle slips into neutral
the vehicle becomes stuck in gear
the transmission makes a loud banging noise
the transmission vibrates excessively.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Slipping or Failure to Engage
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping or failure to engage can cause the vehicle to lose power, slip into neutral, or become stuck in gear, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle slips into neutral
the vehicle fails to engage into gear
the vehicle loses power
the transmission makes a loud banging noise
the transmission vibrates excessively.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The driveshaft noise and vibration can cause premature failure of the driveshaft, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: A loud "howling" noise
like a wet finger around a wine glass
is heard while driving
the noise is dependent on ambient temperature and vehicle speed
the driveshaft vibrates excessively.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly
often when slowing down or braking
the engine revs up
the brake pedal feels soft
and the vehicle may continue to accelerate even when the brake pedal is pressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake failure can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft
the vehicle does not respond to braking
the vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
and the driver may lose control of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electronic throttle control system failure can cause unintended acceleration, loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The engine revs up unexpectedly
the vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly
and the driver may lose control of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The difficulty in shifting out of park position can cause accidents, especially when the vehicle is on an incline or in heavy traffic, and can also lead to transmission damage.
symptoms: Difficulty shifting out of park position
loud noise coming from the front of the vehicle when shifting into drive
strong odor of fuel when refueling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The shimmying of the steering wheel can cause loss of vehicle control, especially at high speeds, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Steering wheel shakes or vibrates while driving
especially at speeds of 35-50mph.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The high-pitched whine noise can be distracting to the driver, causing fatigue and decreased attention to the road, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: High-pitched whine noise similar to running a finger around the rim of a wine glass
noise occurs between 15-20mph and again at 65-70mph.
